    <h2>Type Scale</h2>

    <p>We define a limited set of proportional font sizes: 12px, 14px, 16px, 18px, 24px, 36px, 48px, 60px, and 72px.</p>

    <div class="mds-specimen mds-typescale">
        <h1 class="huge">Size Huge</h1>
        <h1 class="l1">Size Level One</h1>
        <h2 class="l2">Size Level Two</h2>
        <h3 class="l3">Size Level Three</h3>
        <h4 class="l4">Size Level Four</h4>
        <h5 class="l5">Size Level Five</h5>
        <h6 class="l6">Size Level Six</h6>
        <div class="small">Size Small</div>
        <div class="x-small">Size X-Small</div>
    </div>

    <p>We use SCSS mixins to declare these font sizes, and those mixins include media queries to adjust the sizes at key breakpoints. Text gets bigger as the viewport gets bigger.</p>

    <pre class="mds-specimen"><code>
    @include font-size-huge;
    @include font-size-level1;
    @include font-size-level2;
    @include font-size-level3;
    @include font-size-level4;
    @include font-size-level5;
    @include font-size-level6;
    @include font-size-small;
    @include font-size-extra-small;
    </code></pre>
